ImageElement.caption: Livermore-Pleasanton Fire Department firefighters try to extinguish part of a two-alarm structure fire on Normandy Circle in Livermore, Calif., on Friday, May 3, 2013. Propane tanks stored in direct sunlight in the backyard cause the tanks to expand venting gas that found an ignition source starting the fire. Livermore-Pleasanton Fire Department Deputy Chief Joseph Rodondi, advises storing propane tanks in a ventilated, shaded location. Thirty five firefighters responded to the fire and there were no injuries. (Doug Duran/Bay Area News Group)
